# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-2688
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Mark-making: using drawing tools and techniques"@en ;
  curric:slug "mark-making-using-drawing-tools-and-techniques" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit puils will investigate, explore and use a range of materials and
  techniques to create drawings. They will make art expressively and spontaneously,
  exploring texture and pattern with a range of media before before creating drawing
  machines."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Mark-making helps pupils be more articulate and expressive when drawing.
  By discovering how different materials can be controlled, combined and synthesised into
  personal outcomes, pupils can better describe their subject in ways to suit their intentions.
  At this age, pupils are developing their ability to think and act in imaginative ways and
  this unit gives them a greater ability to realise their ideas.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2688-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2688-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2688-3 ;
  curric:id "2688"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.939254Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw .

oakcurric:unit-2692
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Moon and space: drawing and mixed media"@en ;
  curric:slug "moon-and-space-drawing-and-mixed-media" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will develop their ability to apply light and dark tones to shade the
  surface of the moon. They will create a space background and use collage papers of their
  own making to create a planet composition."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces the concept of light and dark tonal shading, which is
  an important foundational concept in the subject and how artists represent form on a flat
  surface. Pupils will have been introduced to basic drawing skills in EYFS and this unit will
  build on those to develop their ability to realise their intentions in mixed media.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2692-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2692-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2692-3 ;
  curric:id "2692"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.767143Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-print .

oakcurric:unit-2700
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "I am beautiful: drawing and mixed media"@en ;
  curric:slug "i-am-beautiful-drawing-and-mixed-media" ;
  rdfs:comment """This is a profile portrait drawing unit that incorporates photographing and
  drawing the face in profile, printing and relief sculpture. Pupils will not only draw the
  face, but celebrate what is unique about themselves incorporating this into their art."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Portraiture is a common, recurring theme in art. This profile portrait
  unit serves as an introduction to the genre. It will serve as a grounding for more complex
  portraiture later in the curriculum. The unit also introduces concepts such as simple
  proportion and a range of art skills in several domains. In addition, the unit asks pupils to
  reflect on themselves and their identiy and in this way, combines skills development with
  ideation and imagination.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2700-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2700-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2700-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2700-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2700-5 ;
  curric:id "2700"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.089175Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt ,
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital .

oakcurric:unit-3830
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Art that travels: stories, land and journeys"@en ;
  curric:slug "art-that-travels-stories-land-and-journeys" ;
  rdfs:comment """Made in collaboration with October Gallery, this unit explores how art shares
  stories across time and place as pupils cut, sculpt and collage maps into textured
  journeys of movement, exchange, identity and belonging."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Each lesson centres on transformation: paper becomes sculpture, maps
  become textured stories, clay becomes travelling figures, and patterns become sails filled
  with meaning. Alongside sensory exploration, pupils encounter stories from the Silk Road to
  West Africa, reimagining borders not as lines but as pathways of exchange. The unit honours
  how ideas and materials travel, celebrating art as a shared language of place, journey, and
  belonging.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3830-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3830-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3830-3 ;
  curric:id "3830"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.246962Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 .

oakcurric:unit-2691
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Create a flower garden: introducing the 7 elements of art"@en ;
  curric:slug "create-a-flower-garden-introducing-the-7-elements-of-art" ;
  rdfs:comment """Through hands-on activities, pupils will experiment with different making
  techniques and materials to create artworks based on the 7 elements of art. Pupils will
  gain a deeper understanding of how artists use the elements within their artworks."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils continue to explore through play, encountering colour, pattern,
  texture, line, shape and form. This unit addresses artistic elements in a creative,
  collaborative manner and embraces a 'make first' materials led approach.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2691-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2691-2 ;
  curric:id "2691"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.393831Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2675
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The seasons: painting and colour mixing"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-seasons-painting-and-colour-mixing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils will develop brush control and knowledge of paint colours,
  techniques & processes. They will experiment with mixing and applying colours in visual
  contexts, for creative effects and to solve problems. They will use a variety of
  techniques to create a seasonal triptych."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Fine motor skill development is crucial at this stage and the development
  of brush control and colour mixing is an important foundation for future success in the
  subject. This unit teaches children to identify primary colours and mix them to make
  secondary colours. Pupils will consider how the same season can be portrayed in a variety of
  ways using a wide range of painting techniques.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2675-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2675-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2675-3 ;
  curric:id "2675"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.611947Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint .

oakcurric:unit-2706
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Me, myself and others: clay sculpture"@en ;
  curric:slug "me-myself-and-others-clay-sculpture" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit examines the pupils’ sense of self and explores their relationships with
  others. They will make clay figures, small drawings and prints as well as collecting
  photos. They will design and make sculptures from a wire armature and masking tape, before
  combining their elements."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils at this stage will be developing a greater sense of self and an
  awareness of the network of the people in their lives that are important to them. This
  conceptual unit develops visual communication skills, and pupils find out how other artists
  and designers have described human relationships.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2706-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2706-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2706-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2706-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2706-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2706-6 ;
  curric:id "2706"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.617566Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt ,
    oakcurric:thread-print .

oakcurric:unit-3829
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My world: art and nature"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-world-art-and-nature" ;
  rdfs:comment """Designed in collaboration with October Gallery, this unit reflects how art
  operates in the world, as expression, storytelling, identity and connection. While
  remaining accessible for all classrooms pupils explore mark-making, movement, clay, print,
  and dye to build fine and gross motor skills."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Children begin by understanding themselves in relation to the natural
  world, laying the foundation for empathy, care for the Earth, and awareness of interconnected
  stories. Early engagement in personal mark-making supports National Curriculum goals in
  exploring ideas and developing control in materials. Nature as archive, self and movement,
  mapping memory, sensory engagement with materials, environmental awareness, shared human
  experience.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3829-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3829-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3829-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3829-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3829-5 ;
  curric:id "3829"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.619416Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 .

oakcurric:unit-2705
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Reclaimed materials: drawing and sculpture"@en ;
  curric:slug "reclaimed-materials-drawing-and-sculpture" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will learn about art made from reclaimed materials. They will explore this
  theme to make their own animal art in two and three dimensions, applying core art skills
  and craft techniques."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops the pupils’ art skills in drawing complex forms such as
  animals and the fine motor skills they need to create models and sculptures. Pupils will
  consider our impact on the environment whilst making sustainable art.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2705-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2705-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2705-3 ;
  curric:id "2705"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.710645Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2703
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Our spaces: drawing and printing"@en ;
  curric:slug "our-spaces-drawing-and-printing" ;
  rdfs:comment """A diverse range of approaches will be used in this unit to investigate houses in
  both an artistic and an architectural style. Drawing and printing techniques will be
  explored before pupils investigate how architects design environmentally friendly houses
  or flats, then design their own eco-home."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces drawing techniques for different purposes to develop
  pupils’ imaginative and design thinking skills. Elements of technical drawing, expressive
  drawing and printing will be introduced and pupils will think about the topic of
  sustainability.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2703-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2703-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2703-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2703-4 ;
  curric:id "2703"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.139906Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-print .

oakcurric:unit-2690
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Watery weavings: introducing textiles"@en ;
  curric:slug "watery-weavings-introducing-textiles" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils learn the principles of weaving and develop their manipulative skills
  through fastening fabric based materials. They investigate and explore the principle of
  textile construction and gain sensory experience of textile materials."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues the theme of investigating materials, it builds on
  prior learning in the EYFS around fine motor control and their observations of the world
  around them. These explorations of textile materials will inform learning in subsequent
  units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2690-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2690-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2690-3 ;
  curric:id "2690"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.383173Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-textiles .

oakcurric:unit-2601
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Reflections on water: introducing painting"@en ;
  curric:slug "reflections-on-water-introducing-painting" ;
  rdfs:comment """Through investigations and studies of a diverse range of artworks based on water,
  pupils will make their own observations and records of the subject. They will make
  collaborative temporary collages based upon the theme of water."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Outcomes in this unit are expressive and open ended, which is an important
  concept in art. This unit challenges the idea that there should be a single outcome or a
  ‘right’ way to complete the task. By emphasising creative explorations and original thought
  this unit demonstrates that there are no right or wrong ways to portray a subject.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2601-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2601-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2601-3 ;
  curric:id "2601"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.547210Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-paint .

oakcurric:unit-2701
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Paradise island: drawing and sculpture"@en ;
  curric:slug "paradise-island-drawing-and-sculpture" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops pupils’ ability to draw expressively and imaginatively in a
  range of media. They will investigate how and why artists create their art, before
  designing and sculpting an imaginary paradise island either individually or
  collaboratively."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on skills being developed in other areas of the
  curriculum such as direction, distance, position and shapes in maths, and using maps,
  direction, aerial and plan perspectives in geography.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2701-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2701-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2701-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2701-4 ;
  curric:id "2701"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.672994Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-3682
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Maps to explore identity, journeys, and imagination."@en ;
  curric:slug "frank-bowling-map-paintings" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore how maps can be used in a different way by artists,
  to tell stories about who we are and where we’ve been. They will create their own personal
  maps, think about identity, places and people that are imporant to them and journeys they
  make."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have already studied the work of artists and makers, in this unit
  they deepen their understanding of how artists work in studio spaces and where they get their
  ideas from. Pupils use their own ideas and experiences to make their own map paintings.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3682-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3682-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3682-3 ;
  curric:id "3682"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.674786Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-print .

